{"type":"message","id":"70a2fcb7","parentId":"8894f0f5","timestamp":"2026-03-04T20:08:46.079Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning."}],"timestamp":1772654926076}}
{"type":"message","id":"e8e3b462","parentId":"70a2fcb7","timestamp":"2026-03-04T20:09:02.336Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user started a new session. According to my instructions, I need to:\n1. Read the required files before responding (SOUL.md, USER.md, memory files)\n2. Greet the user in my configured persona\n3. Keep it 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do\n\nLet me first check if I have any identity configured. Looking at the workspace files provided in the context:\n- IDENTITY.md exists but is empty (no name, creature, vibe, emoji, or avatar filled in)\n- USER.md exists but is empty\n- BOOTSTRAP.md exists - this means I haven't been set up yet!\n\nSince BOOTSTRAP.md exists, I should follow it - it's my \"birth certificate\" according to AGENTS.md. The bootstrap instructions say I should start a conversation to figure out who I am together with the user.\n\nBut wait - the user message says \"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now\". This seems like it could be an automatic message from the system, not an actual user-initiated reset.\n\nLet me re-read the context more carefully. The BOOTSTRAP.md file is in the workspace files, which means this is a fresh workspace. According to AGENTS.md:\n\"If `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\"\n\nSo I should follow the bootstrap process. But the user's actual message appears to be the trigger for the new session. Let me just proceed naturally.\n\nGiven that:\n1. BOOTSTRAP.md exists - this is a fresh workspace\n2. IDENTITY.md is empty - I don't have a name/identity yet\n3. USER.md is empty - I don't know who the user is\n\nI should introduce myself and start the bootstrap conversation as instructed in BOOTSTRAP.md. The runtime model is kilocode/minimax/minimax-m2.5:free and the default_model is also kilocode/minimax/minimax-m2.5:free, so they match - no need to mention that.\n\n\nI'll craft a warm, welcoming greeting that invites the user to collaborate on establishing my identity. I'll keep it concise and personable, focusing on the collaborative nature of this initial conversation.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey! I just came online — fresh workspace, no memories yet. Who am I? Who are you? Let's figure this out together. 🤖"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5:free","usage":{"input":12779,"output":507,"cacheRead":283,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13569,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772654926078}}
